  <span id="freeText10658274421141222166" style="display:none">I loved reading the story. I watched the movie first and I admit it was a mistake. I expected the book to be fast paced too but it wasn't. Even the story is very much different. (SMH). But I guess, that's the best part of being a bibliophile, to be able to know the characters personally; and feel for and with them. I loved the deep and poignant characterization! I deducted one star only because of those too many conversations which lead the story nowhere. This thing can be edited. And I've observed this to be a recurring trait in sparks' novels.</span>
